<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Remarks</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Atriplex spinifera, </i>as with closely related <i>A. confertifolia </i>and <i>A. polycarpa, </i>produces abundant seed that collects in the soil. Little specific information is available about its ecology. <br/>
<br/>
The alliance frequently associates with stands of <i>A. polycarpa, </i>but more immediately adjacent to playas with finer-textured sediments than other <i>Atriplex </i>species. This is the most restricted of the <i>Atriplex</i>-dominated alliances, occupying small areas either adjacent to playas or in large, spreading basins. </div>
</div>

    
	
	
